		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Lytic transition of Epstein-Barr virus ( EBV ) is initiated by distinct immediate early regulators of the viral cycle , in synchronization to temporary , permissive conditions during host cell differentiation . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We developed eukaryotic vectors suitable to imitate the processes involved in lytic transition in cell culture systems . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "Two stable B cell lines were established :",
			"relation": "MANNER-MEANS",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "R59Z activator cells were used",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "to induce lytic EBV expression in a constitutive manner by the production of the BZLF 1 trans-activator ( Zta ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ENABLEMENT",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "R7-57 reporter cells , on the other hand , signaled induced activity of the lytic origin of EBV replication ( ori Lyt ) . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "Different modes , like chemical induction , lytic superinfection with EBV and single gene trans-activation converted the recombinant ori Lyt element in R7-57 reporter cells . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "BZLF 1 , transiently expressed in R7-57 reporter cells , was the only EBV trans-activator found ,",
			"relation": "VERIFICATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "sufficient in inducing the viral lytic cycle . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "Basing on these experiments ,",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "trans-cellular activation of EBV was tested by cocultivation of BZLF 1-expressing R59Z activator cells with the R7-57 reporter line . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "No lytic effect on the reporter cells could be measured , neither by cocultivation of activator cells nor by coincubation of BZLF 1-containing cell lysates . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "Latency breaking activity , however , was transferred from activator to reporter cells",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "when active , exogenous virus was added . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "The cell system described in these experiments provides a tool for the detection of EBV reactivation",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "and demonstrates the potential of the lytic regulatory gene BZLF 1 . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}